ultural forged item called field plate - a different animal altogether.  A Master smith should trivial all the banded items before attempting plate. Banded cloaks now trivial at 175 - money spent on banded trivializing will save you a fortune when you move to plate.  Components needed for plate are folded MW metal sheets, water, a smithy hammer (hammer is reusable even if the combine attempt fails as long as you use the correct recipe) and leather padding (a tailored item using any LQ wolf cat or bear pelt and a silk thread (thread made by combining two spiderling silk)) I have several hundred leather padding stockpiled if you are making plate for a guildmate, let me know.  The big contraint is the MQ folded metal sheets, these cannot be purchased from a merchant and must be smithed at a cost of 22-23 pp each. The components are NOT stackable and the weights are very high, over 60 weight for each sheet with the fished sheet weighing 15.  One sheet is used for the face wrist and neck items, three for the chest back and greaves and two sheets for the rest.  Add in the costs of the molds (not reusable) and you have one expensive, time consuming and weighty attempt. Storgue  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=2d2e3f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bsoulcadre92756.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=voronwe>Voronwe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/30/00 5:25:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plate making</span><hr size=1> ya say you have the leather padding stuff?  When does that trivial?  Also, where do I get the components for folded mq sheets?  I'm gonna be able to make them soon enough, and I could use a few definite things.  As a side note, plate sells for 10-15pp per ac so you can make decent money making it.<br>
<br>
