<br>
I'm rapidly trying to get through banded smithing.  I managed to increase skill 22 points this weekend.  While smithing a few complete sets of banded medium and small.  My character is always on the look out for better wisdom items, currently at 151 wisdom.<br>
<br>
For finding good prices I have a second account I use for friends who are casual gamers when they visit me.  On that account I have a high elf character with a fairly high cha, I believe it's &gt;115 so I get better prices.  One thing I have had problems with is finding good prices on small molds since I usually purchase them in Misty Thicket with my ugly (50 cha) halfing cleric/smith.  I usually leave Edara the high elf where ever I'm purchasing ore with a few hundred (700) stones of ore in inventory.<br>
<br>
One other nice thing I fond about being a cleric and a smith...  when you cannot seem to find someone to buff your str, there is always yaulp II +20 str for a short period of time (18 seconds), long enough to make the run to a forge or bank faster.<br>
<br>
